title: directory listing
extract: di·rec·to·ries. A book containing an alphabetical or classified listing of names, addresses, and other data, such as telephone numbers, of specific persons, groups, or firms. Computers An organizational unit for files that reside on a hard disk or other storage device. Also called folder . A book of rules or directions ...
